article.headline: Jackson might be done for season with knee injury

article.linkText: Brittany Jackson suffers injury as No. 5 Tennessee wins big
article.story:
CAROLINA, Puerto Rico (AP) -- Tennessee (No. 5 ESPN/USA Today; No. 4 Associated Press) might have
lost Brittany Jackson for the rest of the season.

<photo1>

	   Jackson collided with an opponent with 29 seconds left Sunday in
a 75-40 rout of Saint Louis on the final day of the San Juan
Shootout, and the forward might have damaged ligaments in her left
knee.

	   ''It's a big loss,'' coach Pat Summitt said. ''We don't have a
player on our team who can shoot the 3 with the range and quickness
of Brittany.''

	   Tennessee trainer Jenny Moshak said Jackson likely sustained
tears to two ligaments in her left knee.

	   Gwen Jackson and Kara Lawson scored 14 points each to lead Tennessee (5-1), which swept three games in the round-robin
tournament.

	   ''It's helped us a lot,'' said Tennessee's Shyra Ely, who scored
12 points. ''We've grown as a team throughout the tournament.''

	   St. Louis (4-1) trailed 30-22 at halftime, and Tennessee
outscored the Billikens 16-4 at the start of the second half, a
spurt that included two 3-pointers by Gwen Jackson.

	   Tye'sha Fluker capped a 13-0 run with layup off a rebound to
give the Lady Vols a 24-point lead.

	   Lawson scored 10 points in the first half, going 5-for-6 from
the free-throw line. Tennessee had a 14-point run in the first
half, getting 3-pointers from each Jackson, but the Lady
Vols also made 14 turnovers.
